CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 29, 1960, pg. A2, reads: "HOFFA GREETED - More than 1,600 teamsters, a portion of the crowd shown above, turned out last Sunday at Soldiers and Sailors Memorial Hall to greet Teamster Union President James F. (Jimmy) Hoffa. Included in crowd were more than 100 members of Local 609, a predominantly Negro group headed by William E. (Bill) Miller. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Crowd of men and women, some holding Teamsters signs from local 30 and 397, seated in Soldiers and Sailors Memorial Hall for Teamsters rally
